---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { servicePricingFaqs } from '../../data/pricing';
import PageIntro from '../../components/PageIntro.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Google Maps SEO for Restaurants Toronto | Toronto Restaurant Growth"
  description="Google Maps SEO for Toronto and GTA restaurants. Rank in the top 3 for your cuisine and neighbourhood. More searches, more calls, more covers — without ad spend."
>

  <main>

    <!-- HERO -->
    <PageIntro title="Google Maps SEO for Restaurants Toronto" description={'When someone searches "best halal restaurant near me" or "seafood Scarborough," the top 3 results on Google Maps get 70% of the clicks. We get Toronto restaurants into those top 3 spots — and keep them there.'} ctaLabel="Book a Free Google Audit" ctaHref="/contact/" />

    <!-- WHAT WE OPTIMIZE -->
    <section class="bg-white py-16 sm:py-20 lg:py-24"><div class="trg-prose mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <h2>Google Maps SEO Toronto — what we optimize</h2>
        <p>
          Google Maps SEO Toronto restaurants need starts with a complete Google Business Profile, steady review velocity, and a website that sends consistent local signals. We optimize every layer — categories, citations, on-site content, and reporting — so you show up when hungry customers search nearby.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- THE NUMBERS -->
    <section class="bg-white py-16 sm:py-20 lg:py-24"><div class="trg-prose mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <h2>
          Google Maps Is the Most Valuable Real Estate in Your Market
        </h2>

        <div class="trg-stat-grid">
          <div class="trg-stat-card">
            <div class="value">86%</div>
            <div class="label">of people use Google Maps to find restaurants near them</div>
          </div>
          <div class="trg-stat-card">
            <div class="value">70%</div>
            <div class="label">of clicks on Google Maps searches go to the top 3 results</div>
          </div>
          <div class="trg-stat-card">
            <div class="value">$0</div>
            <div class="label">ad spend required — organic Maps ranking is free traffic forever</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- THE PROBLEM -->
    <section class="bg-surface py-16 sm:py-20 lg:py-24"><div class="trg-prose mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <h2>
          Why Most Restaurants Are Invisible on Google
        </h2>

        <h3>Your Google Business Profile is incomplete</h3>
        <p>
          Most restaurant owners claim their Google Business Profile and fill in the basics — name, address, phone number. That's not enough. Google rewards profiles that are fully optimized with consistent NAP data, complete attributes, active photo uploads, Q&A management, and regular posting. An incomplete profile tells Google you're not paying attention.
        </p>

        <h3>Your competitors are outranking you on review velocity</h3>
        <p>
          Google's local ranking algorithm weighs recency and volume of reviews heavily. A restaurant with 200 reviews but none in the last 60 days will lose ground to a competitor actively generating 15+ reviews per month. Review velocity — not just total count — is a major ranking factor.
        </p>

        <h3>Your website isn't supporting your Maps ranking</h3>
        <p>
          Google Maps ranking is partly determined by the strength of your website's local signals. If your site doesn't have location-specific content, structured data markup, and consistent NAP data matching your Maps listing, you're leaving ranking points on the table.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- WHAT WE DO -->
    <section class="bg-white py-16 sm:py-20 lg:py-24"><div class="trg-prose mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <h2>What You Get</h2>

        <h3>Google Business Profile Optimization</h3>
        <p>
          We audit and fully optimize your Google Business Profile — every field, every attribute, every category. We then implement an ongoing management system that keeps your profile active and signals to Google that your restaurant is open, engaged, and relevant.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Category optimization</strong> — primary and secondary categories set for maximum search coverage</li>
          <li><strong>Weekly Google Posts</strong> — specials, events, and promotions posted directly to your Maps listing</li>
          <li><strong>Photo uploads</strong> — regular fresh photography uploaded to your GBP to signal activity</li>
          <li><strong>Q&A management</strong> — common customer questions answered proactively</li>
          <li><strong>Attribute management</strong> — halal, outdoor seating, parking, accessibility — all the filters customers use</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Local Citation Building</h3>
        <p>
          We build and manage consistent citations across every major directory: Yelp, TripAdvisor, Zomato, OpenTable, Facebook, Apple Maps, Bing Places, and dozens of niche directories. Consistent NAP data across the web is a foundational local SEO signal.
        </p>

        <h3>Local SEO Content</h3>
        <p>
          We create location-specific landing pages and content that targets the searches your potential customers are actually making. "Halal biryani Brampton," "best roti Scarborough," "seafood restaurant Mississauga" — every high-intent search in your neighbourhood.
        </p>

        <h3>Rank Tracking & Reporting</h3>
        <p>
          Monthly reports showing your rankings for target keywords across your service area, GBP performance metrics (views, clicks, calls, direction requests), and competitor benchmarks so you always know where you stand.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CASE STUDY -->
    <section class="bg-surface py-16 sm:py-20 lg:py-24"><div class="trg-prose mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <h2>Real Results</h2>
        <div style="border-left: 4px solid #E85D04; padding: 32px; border-radius: 8px; margin: 24px 0; border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1);">
          <p>Position 8 to Position 2 in 6 months</p>
          <p>After implementing our full Google Maps SEO stack for Crab Boil — GBP optimization, review generation, local citations, and weekly posting — their ranking for "seafood restaurant Toronto" jumped from position 8 to position 2. Combined with 280+ reviews, their GBP drives over 1,200 direction requests per month.</p>
          <p><a href="/case-studies/crab-boil/">Read the full Crab Boil case study</a></p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- FAQ -->
    <section class="bg-surface py-16 sm:py-20 lg:py-24"><div class="trg-prose mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

        <div class="trg-faq-item">
          <h3>How much does Google Maps SEO cost for a restaurant in Toronto?</h3>
          <p style="color: #4a4a4a;" set:html={servicePricingFaqs.googleMaps} />
          <p>Most clients see meaningful ranking improvements within 60–90 days.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="trg-faq-item">
          <h3>How long does it take to rank higher on Google Maps?</h3>
          <p>Initial ranking improvements typically appear within 30–60 days for less competitive searches and neighbourhoods. Competitive search terms like "best restaurant downtown Toronto" take 3–6 months of sustained optimization. We'll be honest with you about the timeline for your specific market and keywords at the outset.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="trg-faq-item">
          <h3>Is Google Maps SEO different from regular SEO?</h3>
          <p>Yes — significantly. Google Maps (local pack) ranking is determined by proximity, relevance, and prominence signals that are different from organic website rankings. Both matter, and they support each other. But Google Maps is specifically about your Google Business Profile, review velocity, local citations, and local content signals.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="trg-faq-item">
          <h3>Do I need a website for Google Maps SEO to work?</h3>
          <p>You don't strictly need one, but a strong website significantly amplifies your Maps ranking. We recommend building them together — the website's local SEO signals support the Maps ranking, and the Maps listing drives traffic to the website. Standalone GBP optimization without a website will plateau faster.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="trg-faq-item">
          <h3>What are restaurant SEO services for Toronto restaurants?</h3>
          <p>Restaurant SEO services for Toronto restaurants combine Google Business Profile optimization, local citations, review velocity, and location-specific website content — the signals Google uses to decide who appears in the Maps pack. For Mystic Caribbean in Brampton, that stack moved them to #1 on Kennedy Road with 15 keywords in the top 10. <a href="/case-studies/mystic-caribbean/">See the Mystic Caribbean case study</a> for the full breakdown.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="trg-faq-item">
          <h3>Do you offer Google Maps ranking services in Toronto?</h3>
          <p>Yes — we offer Google Maps ranking services in Toronto and across the GTA, from GBP setup through ongoing rank tracking and reporting. Our work with Mystic Caribbean shows what's possible when Maps, reviews, and on-site SEO work together: dominant local visibility with a live dashboard that proves ROI. <a href="/case-studies/mystic-caribbean/">Read the Mystic Caribbean case study</a>.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <section class="bg-surface py-16 sm:py-20 lg:py-24"><div class="trg-prose mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 text-center sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <h2>Your Competitors Are Showing Up. Are You?</h2>
        <p>
          Every day you're not in the top 3 on Google Maps, you're invisible to hundreds of customers searching for exactly what you serve. Start with a free audit — we'll show you exactly where you stand.
        </p>
        <a href="/contact/">
          Book a Free Google Audit
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>
</BaseLayout>
